article.description: — David Roddy had 22 points and 12 rebounds as Colorado State easily beat Air Force 74-44 on Monday night.
article.headline: Roddy scores 22 to carry Colorado St. past Air Force 74-44
article.linkText: Roddy scores 22 to carry Colorado St. past Air Force 74-44
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- — David Roddy had 22 points and 12 rebounds as Colorado State easily beat Air Force 74-44 on Monday night. Isaiah Stevens had 15 points for Colorado State (16-4, 13-3 Mountain West Conference), which won its fourth straight game. Kendle Moore added 10 points. Adam Thistlewood had nine rebounds. Chris Joyce had 10 points for the Falcons (5-19, 3-17). Joseph Octave added six rebounds. The Rams improve to 2-0 against the Falcons this season. Colorado State defeated Air Force 72-49 on Saturday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
